==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cerberus
<hw>Cer"be*rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. Cerberus (in
sense 1), gr. <?/.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>A monster, in the shape of
a three-headed dog, guarding the entrance into the infernal regions,
Hence: Any vigilant custodian or guardian, esp. if surly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of East Indian serpents,
allied to the pythons; the bokadam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cercal</ent>⟦br⟧
